Luo Kun Kun was expelled from his village when locals signed a petition to banish him to 'protect villagers' health' He was diagnosed with HIV when he was five years old . 
  The boy was refused admission to schools and forced to play alone in the woods . 
  He has now been admitted to a specialist school in Linfen, China . 
  The Red Ribbon School is the only school in China equipped to educate HIV-positive children . 
 